# Live in community

![](data:image/png;base64,)

## Overview
Live in community is a tactic, skill, or tool used in public and social innovation work.

## Purpose
The purpose of live in community is to understand the issues and needs of a community by immersing oneself within it.

## How it works
This tactic involves sending individuals into a community for an extended period (e.g., 3 months) to integrate with local residents, understand their challenges, and develop solutions that address these issues.

## Requirements
A deep understanding of the development needs of a community is required to effectively use this tactic. Additionally, a willingness to immerse oneself in the community and engage with its members is essential.

## Reflections
When using live in community as a tactic, it's crucial to remember that building trust and relationships takes time. It's also essential to be open-minded and willing to adapt to new situations.

## Related methods (if any)
This tactic can be used in conjunction with other methods such as community asset mapping, ethnography, or participatory design.

Examples of live in community include sending individuals into a community for an extended period to understand its needs and develop solutions that address these issues.
